A couple was tied up and robbed of valuables during a house robbery in Malmesbury, north of Cape Town, in the early hours of Monday. Police spokesperson Sgt Noloyiso Rwexana said the couple was sleeping when they heard a noise at their front door around 3am. They were attacked by three armed men, two carrying firearms and the third a crowbar. Rwexana said they were tied up while the men stole various items. The husband sustained a head injury. The robbers fled the scene on foot. No arrests had been made. A case of house robbery was opened.